%S A396721 1,1,1,2,1,2,1,5,2,2,1,5,1,2,1,13,1,5,1,5,2,2,1,15,2,2,5,4,1,4,1,44,1,
%T A396721 2,1,14,1,2,2,14,1,6,1,4,2,2,1,50,2,5,1,5,1,14,2,13,2,2,1,13,1,2,4,
%U A396721 191,1,4,1,5,1,4,1,50,1,2,3,4,1,6,1
%N A396721 Number of 3-generated groups of order n: groups that have a generating set of size <= 3.
%C A396721 First differs from A066389 when n=16. Verified in SageMath with GAP extension for groups of order up to 767 excluding 512.
%e A396721 a(p)=1 for p prime since the unique group of order p is cyclic.
%e A396721 a(4)=2 because the cyclic group of order 4 is cyclic and the Klein-4 group can be generated by 2 elements.
%e A396721 a(8)=5 because there are 5 groups of order 8 and all can be generated by three elements.
%e A396721 a(16)=13 because there are 14 groups of order 16 and only (C_2)^4 cannot be generated by three elements.
%o A396721 (SageMath) lambda n : sum([len(sage.interfaces.gap.gap.MinimalGeneratingSet(G)) <= 3 for G in sage.interfaces.gap.gap(n).AllSmallGroups()])
%Y A396721 Cf. A066389.
%K A396721 nonn,new
%O A396721 1,4
%A A396721 _Adam Onus_, Jun 03 2026
